WEBVTT

00:09.593 --> 00:11.094
You said
you'd always watch out for me!

00:11.095 --> 00:13.304
- You promised!
- Well, maybe I don't want to look at ya.

00:13.305 --> 00:14.305
I hate you.

00:14.306 --> 00:16.641
- Zoe, uh, you remember my son, Ryan.
- Hi.

00:16.642 --> 00:18.476
Your father wasn't having an affair
with your mother.

00:18.477 --> 00:20.478
- Grace!
- He raped her.

00:20.479 --> 00:21.981
No!

00:22.565 --> 00:23.523
Oh, my God, Sameer.

00:23.524 --> 00:26.234
-  Is that Zoe's dad?
- Yes.

00:26.235 --> 00:29.237
I would never let anything happen
to you or Zoe.

00:33.451 --> 00:35.285
Sameer's done it.
As of last week,

00:35.286 --> 00:36.411
that naughty little bug of his

00:36.412 --> 00:38.372
is finally strong enough
to top Homelander.

00:39.540 --> 00:41.166
I want you to find William Butcher.

00:41.167 --> 00:42.834
We've got an uber virus,

00:42.835 --> 00:45.086
strong enough to kill every fucking Supe

00:45.087 --> 00:46.838
- on the planet.
- No.

00:46.839 --> 00:48.548
Soldier Boy
killed my family.

00:48.549 --> 00:50.717
I gotta get this motherfucker
outta my head.

00:50.718 --> 00:51.968
Look, you let me go,

00:51.969 --> 00:53.386
you'll be the hero

00:53.387 --> 00:55.222
that saved Translucent.

00:57.141 --> 00:59.184
Sweet boy.

00:59.185 --> 01:01.728
I will be there for you always.

01:01.729 --> 01:02.646
Okay, good.

01:03.981 --> 01:06.525
Why does everyone
keep leaving me?

01:07.276 --> 01:10.278
Stand up,
in the name of Jesus!

01:10.279 --> 01:12.239
My sweet boy.

01:36.639 --> 01:39.265
This doesn't look like
a CIA black site to me.

01:39.266 --> 01:40.183
Oh really,

01:40.184 --> 01:42.018
Command didn't ask your opinion?

01:42.019 --> 01:42.895
Shut up.

02:53.299 --> 02:54.508
Please...

02:55.342 --> 02:56.718
...I have family.

02:56.719 --> 02:58.137
I love Imagine Dragons.

02:59.179 --> 03:00.138
Please.

03:00.139 --> 03:01.264
I'm sorry.

03:01.265 --> 03:02.975
No one can know I was here.

03:08.606 --> 03:09.814
Soldier Boy.

03:09.815 --> 03:12.025
America's first hero.

03:12.026 --> 03:15.737
Defender of liberty, faith and family.

03:15.738 --> 03:18.239
-Branded a traitor by the Legacy Media.

03:18.240 --> 03:20.950
Scapegoated by Starlight, who was

03:20.951 --> 03:23.162
the real mastermind
behind the attack on Seven Tower.

03:24.538 --> 03:26.915
But from the ashes of injustice,

03:26.916 --> 03:29.834
Soldier Boy has been reborn.

03:29.835 --> 03:32.295
And America deserves the truth.

03:32.296 --> 03:33.755
Since 1984,

03:33.756 --> 03:35.506
Soldier Boy has been in Russia,

03:35.507 --> 03:37.133
workin' with our friends in the Kremlin

03:37.134 --> 03:39.719
to root out those sneaky traitors
in Ukraine.

03:39.720 --> 03:42.221
Turns out Russia isn't our enemy.

03:42.222 --> 03:43.890
They're a strong, family-first nation

03:43.891 --> 03:45.808
who don't put up with trans bathrooms.

03:45.809 --> 03:49.103
We're grateful to Soldier Boy
for his courage and sacrifice.

03:49.104 --> 03:51.356
And we hope that he can forgive us

03:51.357 --> 03:53.483
as he takes his rightful place

03:53.484 --> 03:55.069
on The Seven.

03:57.821 --> 04:00.573
It is my honor to present Soldier Boy

04:00.574 --> 04:03.993
with the first ever Democratic Medal
of Patriotic Freedom.

04:16.590 --> 04:17.799
My boy.

04:17.800 --> 04:19.468
My poor, sweet boy.

04:22.680 --> 04:26.516
I'm also very proud to say

04:26.517 --> 04:28.142
that this great hero

04:28.143 --> 04:29.268
is my father.

04:30.521 --> 04:31.980
Whoa, hold on.
When did you find out?

04:36.193 --> 04:38.403
Are there any plans for a team-up?

04:49.123 --> 04:51.499
Forty years out of the spotlight,
you still got it, huh?

04:53.168 --> 04:56.963
Sage tells me, uh,
socials are blowing up.

04:56.964 --> 05:00.008
People magazine,
they're-they're calling us, uh,

05:00.009 --> 05:01.885
America's sexiest dynasty.

05:02.678 --> 05:04.221
You believe that?

05:08.851 --> 05:10.102
Come on.

05:10.811 --> 05:12.228
I would never have sent you in there

05:12.229 --> 05:14.522
if I knew that Butcher had the virus.
I wouldn't have.

05:14.523 --> 05:16.065
Swear to God.

05:16.066 --> 05:19.610
Although,
I did tell you not to engage, so...

05:19.611 --> 05:21.654
if we're pointing fingers, I don't think

05:21.655 --> 05:23.781
I should be exclusively at fault here.

05:23.782 --> 05:25.616
Gentlemen.

05:25.617 --> 05:27.036
Lab results are in.

05:27.786 --> 05:29.163
Lab results.

05:30.164 --> 05:32.790
 Now, a lot has happened
today at this event.

05:32.791 --> 05:35.043
-Soldier Boy's addition...
- How?

05:35.044 --> 05:38.129
We were there, they all got infected.
We watched them die.

05:38.130 --> 05:39.255
How the fuck

05:39.256 --> 05:40.924
is that cunt still breathin'?

05:41.800 --> 05:44.470
Oh, no. Oh, no.

05:50.559 --> 05:52.185
He's got V1 in his bloodstream.

05:52.186 --> 05:54.396
- Shit.
- V1? What is V1?

05:55.731 --> 05:58.525
Frederick Vought's first iteration
of Compound V.

06:00.277 --> 06:03.154
V1's ten times more potent
than today's formula.

06:03.155 --> 06:04.614
Highly unstable.

06:04.615 --> 06:07.325
Only worked on a handful of early Supes:

06:07.326 --> 06:10.661
you, Bombsight,
Torpedo, Private Angel,

06:10.662 --> 06:12.872
Stormfront.

06:12.873 --> 06:15.625
- Who is Stormfront?
- Dr. Vought's wife Clara.

06:15.626 --> 06:17.002
Uh, I think you knew her as Liberty?

06:18.754 --> 06:21.255
Point is, V1 saved your life.

06:21.256 --> 06:23.966
And is likely why
your generation of Supes doesn't age.

06:23.967 --> 06:28.387
This is a modern Compound V molecule.

06:28.388 --> 06:30.515
This is the virus.

06:30.516 --> 06:33.392
Its spike proteins bind
to the V receptors,

06:33.393 --> 06:35.061
kind of like gears meshing.

06:35.062 --> 06:37.022
But V1 is different, it looks like this.

06:39.942 --> 06:41.692
Nothing for the virus to bind to.

06:41.693 --> 06:43.486
You might've told us that
before we tested it.

06:43.487 --> 06:46.030
V1 hasn't been in circulation
since the 1950s.

06:46.031 --> 06:47.490
And I thought Soldier Boy was dead.

06:47.491 --> 06:48.866
We all did.

06:48.867 --> 06:52.870
And now all I'm hearin' is that
this motherfucker is unkillable.

06:52.871 --> 06:54.455
Hmm.

07:03.841 --> 07:05.883
Okay, but what about Homelander?
Does this...

07:05.884 --> 07:07.426
does this mean that...

07:07.427 --> 07:10.054
I'm his son. Am I immune, too?

07:10.055 --> 07:11.347
No.

07:11.348 --> 07:14.016
Your embryo was shot up
with plain old garden-variety V.

07:14.017 --> 07:15.476
Like me, like every other Supe.

07:15.477 --> 07:18.354
But if Homelander got his hands
on some V1, then, theoretically,

07:18.355 --> 07:19.772
he'd be like Soldier Boy.

07:19.773 --> 07:22.108
Immune to the virus.
Maybe even immortal.

07:22.109 --> 07:23.442
- Bring me some.
-  I can't.

07:23.443 --> 07:25.027
- Why not?
- Vought destroyed every vial.

07:25.028 --> 07:26.028
There's none left.

07:26.029 --> 07:28.364
Could a vial still exist somewhere?

07:28.365 --> 07:29.323
I suppose.

07:29.324 --> 07:31.951
Wait. If that's true,
then that means he can use that to--

07:31.952 --> 07:34.203
We need to get to it
before Homelander does.

07:34.204 --> 07:36.372
How? I'm sure he knows all this already.

07:36.373 --> 07:38.666
- We're fucked.
- Good point, luv.

07:38.667 --> 07:40.668
We hit 'em with the virus today,

07:40.669 --> 07:42.170
while it still works.

07:42.171 --> 07:44.213
That wasn't at all my point.

07:44.214 --> 07:45.339
Butcher's right.

07:45.340 --> 07:46.883
See?

07:46.884 --> 07:49.427
It's the smart play. We draw him out

07:49.428 --> 07:51.470
- and hit him today.
-  Okay.

07:51.471 --> 07:52.680
How you gonna get it in front of him?

07:52.681 --> 07:55.975
Homelander hasn't been seen
outside of the Tower in days,

07:55.976 --> 07:58.352
which means
he's probably scared of getting infected.

07:58.353 --> 08:00.271
And if you release this thing,
he just flies up

08:00.272 --> 08:02.232
into fucking space
until it's all over, right?

08:03.817 --> 08:05.109
So until you figure that out,

08:05.110 --> 08:07.820
we have to find some of this V1.

08:07.821 --> 08:09.281
We don't really have a choice.

08:10.282 --> 08:11.408
I know where to start.

08:15.078 --> 08:16.162
Wow.

08:16.163 --> 08:19.373
Thank God that stuff's in you
and saved you. Um...

08:19.374 --> 08:21.834
- Guess all's well that ends well.
- Yeah, well, fuck you.

08:21.835 --> 08:23.628
You knew Butcher had the virus.

08:23.629 --> 08:26.422
You defrosted me just to send me
into the fucking woodchipper.

08:26.423 --> 08:28.507
No. No, I did not.

08:28.508 --> 08:30.718
- What I wanted--
- Well, joke's on you, asshole.

08:30.719 --> 08:32.095
Cause I'm gonna live...

08:32.804 --> 08:34.263
...and you'll die.

08:34.264 --> 08:36.724
If the virus doesn't get you, time will.

08:36.725 --> 08:38.351
And when you're sitting
in that wheelchair,

08:38.352 --> 08:40.019
shitting in a colostomy bag,

08:40.020 --> 08:42.438
I'll be running The Seven,

08:42.439 --> 08:45.234
shitting on Shari Lewis's tits.

08:47.569 --> 08:49.071
Look at you.

08:50.572 --> 08:53.408
Just the softest, wettest boy.

08:55.160 --> 08:57.036
You're pathetic.

08:57.037 --> 08:58.247
You're nothing at all.

09:06.129 --> 09:08.548
Mademoiselle Annie,
are you certain of this?

09:09.675 --> 09:10.716
We don't have a choice.

09:19.810 --> 09:21.519
You know what this means, right?

09:21.520 --> 09:24.772
If we do get this V1,
you and Kimiko could take some.

09:24.773 --> 09:26.857
I mean, it made Soldier Boy
immune to the virus.

09:26.858 --> 09:28.651
It could make you immune, too.
Like a vaccine.

09:28.652 --> 09:30.736
Yeah, or we could grow a million dicks.

09:30.737 --> 09:33.155
Like a Koosh ball, but with dicks.

09:33.156 --> 09:35.742
Very specific.
But look, there's a chance.

09:36.868 --> 09:39.370
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no. No.

09:39.371 --> 09:40.413
No, no, no.

09:40.414 --> 09:41.497
- Not you again.
-  Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

09:41.498 --> 09:43.583
- Zoe, take it easy.
-  Put 'em away, kiddo.

09:44.418 --> 09:46.378
That won't be necessary.

09:47.587 --> 09:49.547
At least, not yet.

09:49.548 --> 09:50.881
Starlight.

09:50.882 --> 09:52.258
We weren't expecting you.

09:52.259 --> 09:54.302
I take it Marie Moreau is running late?

09:54.303 --> 09:55.678
Marie's not coming.

09:55.679 --> 09:57.763
But I know about the meeting
you had a while back.

09:57.764 --> 09:59.975
She set this up, actually.

10:00.559 --> 10:02.435
- Did she?
-  Yeah, we need you

10:02.436 --> 10:04.854
to tell us everything that you know
about V1.

10:04.855 --> 10:07.606
You mean the first generation V

10:07.607 --> 10:10.109
Soldier Boy has in his veins
that made him immune

10:10.110 --> 10:12.487
to the virus you're working on
with William Butcher?

10:15.407 --> 10:18.117
You can't actually be surprised I know.

10:18.118 --> 10:20.870
But why should I help
the friends of a deranged man

10:20.871 --> 10:22.413
who murdered my daughter

10:22.414 --> 10:24.124
and orphaned my granddaughter?

10:27.210 --> 10:28.753
Vicky meant a lot to me, too.

10:28.754 --> 10:31.630
And what Butcher did was unforgivable,
which is why he's not here.

10:31.631 --> 10:33.050
But you're still working with him.

10:34.634 --> 10:38.179
We think that Homelander's trying
to get at V1.

10:38.180 --> 10:41.098
And if he does, he lives forever

10:41.099 --> 10:44.436
and you will be just as fucked
as the rest of us.

10:45.479 --> 10:48.731
So you gonna keep dronin' on
like some fuckin' Black Mr. Spock,

10:48.732 --> 10:50.108
or you gonna help us out?

10:56.615 --> 10:57.948
Follow me.

11:09.127 --> 11:10.420
After you.

11:33.151 --> 11:35.820
Point one percent torch the world,

11:35.821 --> 11:39.156
and watch it burn
from their luxury bunkers.

11:39.157 --> 11:41.325
It smells in here.

11:41.326 --> 11:44.495
You're right. Smells like an Abercrombie
got fucked by a 7-Eleven

11:44.496 --> 11:46.872
while Arby's jerked off in the corner.

11:46.873 --> 11:48.416
It's V-Bro Mango Thunder Body Spray.

11:48.417 --> 11:49.417
Fuck!

11:49.418 --> 11:51.419
Everyone, this is Maverick.

11:51.420 --> 11:52.629
Translucent's son.

11:53.922 --> 11:55.548
'Sup, playa?

11:55.549 --> 11:57.216
'Sup...

11:57.217 --> 11:58.342
playa?

11:58.343 --> 12:01.178
Starlight. I was a kid last you saw me.

12:01.179 --> 12:02.847
You sang at my dad's funeral.

12:02.848 --> 12:04.890
Maverick, hi. Um...

12:04.891 --> 12:08.060
What are you doing here?
Don't you go to Godolkin?

12:08.061 --> 12:09.311
Fuck that place.

12:09.312 --> 12:11.147
And fuck Vought.
They're all a bunch of liars.

12:11.148 --> 12:14.066
They said a cartel super-villain killed
my dad.

12:14.067 --> 12:15.902
Mr. Edgar was the only one
that told me the truth.

12:19.448 --> 12:20.907
It was Homelander.

12:21.908 --> 12:23.910
Homelander killed my dad.

12:26.830 --> 12:28.998
Wow. Homelander?

12:28.999 --> 12:31.083
Ugh, God. I...

12:31.084 --> 12:33.627
Fuck that fucking motherfucker.

12:33.628 --> 12:35.838
I've been saying it for years.
This fucking...

12:35.839 --> 12:37.047
This...

12:37.048 --> 12:38.799
- ...motherfucker.
- Fucking guy. Yeah.

12:38.800 --> 12:42.928
Okay, so...
Maverick, Zoe, Marie Moreau?

12:42.929 --> 12:44.972
What, are you tryin' to start
your own Teenage Kix or somethin'?

12:44.973 --> 12:47.808
I believe the children are our future.

12:47.809 --> 12:50.269
Maverick...
if you'll excuse us a moment?

12:50.270 --> 12:51.479
Follow me.

12:51.480 --> 12:53.772
If you want to know about V1,

12:53.773 --> 12:55.775
I hope that you have strong stomachs.

12:57.235 --> 12:59.820
V1 was barbaric and unstable.

12:59.821 --> 13:02.615
Dr. Vought's first test subjects at Dachau

13:02.616 --> 13:04.909
lived in a state of endless torment.

13:04.910 --> 13:08.162
He murdered thousands,
only to achieve five successes.

13:08.163 --> 13:09.246
Jesus.

13:09.247 --> 13:11.832
Even after Vought defected to the Allies,

13:11.833 --> 13:15.252
he kept testing V1 on a ready supply
of U.S. servicemen.

13:15.253 --> 13:16.921
Why am I not surprised?

13:16.922 --> 13:19.381
By then, we were in an arms race
with the Russians,

13:19.382 --> 13:22.385
so nothing could stand in the way
of national security.

13:23.428 --> 13:26.472
Dr. Vought stabilized the formula
in the '50s

13:26.473 --> 13:28.766
and swept all mention of V1 under the rug,

13:28.767 --> 13:30.726
like every other sordid chapter
in this company's history.

13:30.727 --> 13:33.604
And you're sure there are
no more doses left whatsoever?

13:33.605 --> 13:34.772
Not that I've seen.

13:34.773 --> 13:37.942
You think Vought wanted
a paper trail to Dachau?

13:37.943 --> 13:40.903
This is every surviving file
from Frederick Vought's.

13:40.904 --> 13:42.154
If you want to look through them,

13:42.155 --> 13:43.573
be my guest.

13:49.246 --> 13:51.664
Zoe... Zoe, wait.

13:53.333 --> 13:55.085
What happened to your mom was awful.

13:56.628 --> 13:58.296
Look, I didn't know
that Butcher was gonna...

14:00.257 --> 14:01.800
I didn't mean for her to get hurt.

14:02.884 --> 14:04.261
I promise.

14:09.057 --> 14:10.558
Promise?

14:10.559 --> 14:12.977
You promised that we'd be safe.

14:12.978 --> 14:14.728
Then I woke up alone

14:14.729 --> 14:16.397
to see my mom ripped in half.

14:16.398 --> 14:18.148
- I'm sorry.
- Then I got chucked

14:18.149 --> 14:20.485
into Red River because
my dad is probably dead, too.

14:21.945 --> 14:23.905
So go fuck yourself.

14:36.001 --> 14:37.710
Maybe if I had raised you,

14:37.711 --> 14:39.336
I could've made you better.

14:39.337 --> 14:41.171
You're a fucking disappointment.

14:41.172 --> 14:42.923
...disappointment.

14:42.924 --> 14:45.718
The pitiful disappointment you are.

14:45.719 --> 14:47.928
Deep down,
there's a part of you that is still

14:47.929 --> 14:49.555
- human.
- You're pathetic.

14:49.556 --> 14:51.015
- ♪ ♪
- Weak.

14:51.016 --> 14:52.349
You're my greatest failure.

14:52.350 --> 14:53.601
You're nothing at all.

14:53.602 --> 14:56.062
♪ ♪

15:11.786 --> 15:12.912
Madelyn?

15:13.496 --> 15:15.040
Oh, my boy.

15:16.041 --> 15:17.374
My sweet boy.

15:19.377 --> 15:21.086
What is wrong?

15:21.087 --> 15:22.671
Why are you so unhappy?

15:22.672 --> 15:24.089
My father...

15:24.090 --> 15:26.383
and my son...

15:26.384 --> 15:29.136
Everything. It's all fallen apart.

15:29.137 --> 15:30.763
No.

15:30.764 --> 15:33.058
No, it's exactly what needed to happen.

15:33.808 --> 15:36.435
Yes. It's been foretold.

15:36.436 --> 15:38.604
You're about to ascend.

15:38.605 --> 15:40.147
Become immortal.

15:40.148 --> 15:41.440
Divine.

15:41.441 --> 15:43.233
A true god.

15:43.234 --> 15:44.861
With the love of the world.

15:45.904 --> 15:47.404
- But...
- I know.

15:47.405 --> 15:49.948
You think love is weak and human.

15:49.949 --> 15:52.035
But who is more loved than Jesus?

15:54.120 --> 15:57.082
And why should He have
more love than you?

15:58.166 --> 15:59.876
You save more people than He does.

16:02.337 --> 16:05.464
The one true God.

16:05.465 --> 16:06.424
Yes...

16:07.217 --> 16:08.551
But how?

16:09.761 --> 16:12.262
How? Millions of people just hate me.

16:12.263 --> 16:16.308
Well, then, you baptize the unfaithful
in their own blood.

16:18.395 --> 16:21.647
- Rip babies from their mothers' wombs.
- Yes...

16:21.648 --> 16:24.858
Skin parents in front of their children.

16:24.859 --> 16:28.320
- Rid the world of the wicked.
- Yes...

16:28.321 --> 16:29.656
The non-believers.

16:32.075 --> 16:33.784
They'll call me a monster.

16:33.785 --> 16:36.621
No. The only ones left
will be your faithful.

16:37.664 --> 16:39.581
And they will love you in their hearts.

16:40.750 --> 16:43.503
They'll cry happy tears
at the mere thought of you.

16:44.838 --> 16:47.673
You have one last task, my love.

16:47.674 --> 16:48.675
Yes.

16:57.475 --> 17:00.394
Ah...!

17:18.872 --> 17:19.955
You're late.

17:19.956 --> 17:21.665
Came as soon as you texted.

17:21.666 --> 17:22.708
Was kinda far.

17:22.709 --> 17:24.543
- Where?
- Russia.

17:24.544 --> 17:26.253
Near the border, I think.

17:26.254 --> 17:27.547
Anybody see you?

17:28.965 --> 17:30.300
Uh, no.

17:31.968 --> 17:33.011
What's that?

17:39.392 --> 17:40.809
Uh...

17:40.810 --> 17:42.395
cut myself shaving.

17:43.396 --> 17:45.856
Trust me, you don't need to shave.

17:50.028 --> 17:53.323
Uh, so your... your grandpa's in there
with them now?

17:54.657 --> 17:56.450
Is, uh...

17:56.451 --> 17:58.076
is-is Butcher in there?

17:58.077 --> 17:59.161
No.

17:59.162 --> 18:01.246
But they can lead us to him.

18:01.247 --> 18:03.540
We can find him and kill him.

18:03.541 --> 18:05.584
Kill Butcher?

18:05.585 --> 18:08.128
I-I don't...
I don't think that's a good idea.

18:08.129 --> 18:09.338
You don't think we could?

18:09.339 --> 18:11.298
He's dangerous.

18:11.299 --> 18:12.841
Look what he did to your mom.

18:12.842 --> 18:14.426
That's the point.

18:14.427 --> 18:15.844
- He's not worth it.
- Ryan...

18:15.845 --> 18:17.347
It's not worth you getting hurt.

18:18.848 --> 18:21.017
He'd kill you.

18:22.393 --> 18:25.062
So I'm just supposed to fly away
and hide with my dick in my hand?

18:25.063 --> 18:26.481
- Zoe--
- Forget it.

18:43.832 --> 18:46.918
You think I couldn't smell
the Tanqueray on your breath?

18:49.254 --> 18:50.379
What the fuck?

18:50.380 --> 18:51.381
Well, well, well.

18:52.048 --> 18:54.716
Ain't this my lucky fuckin' day?

18:54.717 --> 18:56.344
Should buy meself a lotto ticket.

18:57.345 --> 18:59.513
Thought you'd still be
in touch with your girl.

18:59.514 --> 19:00.722
And if I hadn't showed?

19:00.723 --> 19:03.851
